						<div class="postbody">Here's an updated version of the test program - <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nocash.emubase.de/nss-test.zip">http://nocash.emubase.de/nss-test.zip</a><!-- m --><br />It's inserting a new OUT [72h],59h prior to the old OUT [72h],C3h chip-selection.<br />The NSS BIOS is doing the same thing.<br />Most of the databits are just cryptic random-garbage, but I think that bit6 is CLK, that might be important to be switched high BEFORE setting chipselect to low (which is probably done via bit4).<br />If that is fixing the OSD output, then I am having a massive problem with initial CLK levels... it's a bit similar to my PROM problem with CLK occuring upon releasing RESET.</div>

